        <figure>
            <img src="img/case-studies/cft/cftLogoOption4.svg"
                alt="Logo option for Cards for Today based on an Ace in a deck of cards with a flipped over A in Today oriented horizontally">
            <figcaption>The final logo for Cards for Today</figcaption>
        </figure>
        <p>After meeting the bandmembers and learning about them, the bands' personality felt very solid and
            traditional, so I knew right away that a chunky slab serif typeface was the way to go. Along with that, they
            still have flare, so I wanted to stylize the <i>For</i> to make it feel more in line with some 1920's packaging.
        </p>
        <p>I also wanted to call back to a deck of cards. What better card than the most iconic Ace of Spades! So I flipped the A in <i>Today</i>.</p>
        <h3>Color</h3>
        <div class="color-palette-group gap-v gap-h">
