                    </svg>
                    <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
                        <circle cx="50%" cy="50%" r="49%" />
                    </svg>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <p>I chose these colors as they are the same as on a standard deck of playing cards. White as the base card,
            black for spades and clubs, and red for diamonds and hearts. In one of our review calls, I jokingly asked if
            the bandmembers knew about how some decks used to come with a <a
                href="https://deckofshields.com/five-suit-decks/">fifth suit</a>, but we agreed that adding a fourth
            color would just complicate the design further.</p>
